# SEMANTIC VIOLATION TEST
# This circuit exposes the lack of two-phase signal update.
#
# Circuit:
#   B = NOT A
#   C = A AND B
#   D = NOT C
#
# When A changes from 0→1:
#   CORRECT (VHDL semantics):
#     All processes at same delta see OLD values.
#     AND sees old B=1, computes C = 1 AND 1 = 1
#     Then next delta: AND sees new B=0, computes C = 1 AND 0 = 0
#     C going 0→1→0 triggers NOT_C twice, D ends up = 1
#
#   BUGGY (current simulator):
#     If NOT fires before AND at same delta:
#       NOT sets B=0 immediately
#       AND sees UPDATED B=0, computes C = 1 AND 0 = 0 (no change)
#       C never transitions, NOT_C never fires, D stays 0
#       FINAL VALUE IS WRONG: D=0 instead of D=1

signal A 0
signal B 1
signal C 0
signal D 0

not B A
and C A B
not D C
